questions.prompt: At the conclusion of World War II, the Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia emerged as a federation of six constituent republics. Which one of the six is missing from this unordered list? Macedonia, Croatia, Serbia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Montenegro.
